OCSort 1.0.0 

OCSort is an open source sort tool, which implement a subset of the functionnality of the Microfocus(c) MFSORT(c) utility.

This program is distributed under the GNU General Public License. See COPYING for details.

OCSort requires the following external libraries to be installed:
  GNUCOBOL (1.1.0)  LIBCOB
  GNUCOBOL (1.1.0)  MPIR

Functionnality supported :
___________________________________________________________________________________    
 OCSort	Help                                                                       
___________________________________________________________________________________
 Syntax = Uppercase sensitive                                                      
___________________________________________________________________________________
Usage with file parameters   : OCSORT TAKE filename          
    filename is textfile with command for sort. 
    For comment into file put '*' in first column.                      
___________________________________________________________________________________
Usage with command line                                                            
OCSORT                                                                             
	SORT | MERGE                                                                   
		FIELDS (start,length,type,[A|D], ...)           |                          
		FIELDS ((start,length,type,[A|D], ...),FORMAT=TYPE	|                 	       
		FIELDS=COPY 							                          	       
	USE  FILENAME ORG [LS|SQ|SQMF] RECORD [[F,Record Len] | [V,MIN,MAX Record Len]]
	GIVE FILENAME ORG [LS|SQ|SQMF] RECORD [[F,Record Len] | [V,MIN,MAX Record Len]]
	INCLUDE|OMIT COND=(CONDITION) [FORMAT=TYPE]                                    
	   (CONDITION) (pos,len,type,cond,[AND|OR],pos,len,type)					   
	               (pos,len,type,cond,[X|C|Z]'[value]')							   
	               (cond,[AND|OR],cond)											   
	INREC FIELDS=(FIELD-SPEC...)                                                   
	SUM FIELDS = (pos,len,type, ...)                                               
	SUM FIELDS = (NONE)  or   SUM FIELDS = NONE									   
	OUTREC FIELDS=(FIELD-SPEC...)                                                  
	OUTFIL                                                                         
		FILES/FNAMES= (enviroment variable)                                        
		STARTREC=nn                                                                
		ENDREC=nn                                                                  
		[SAVE|[INCLUDE|OMIT] (CONDITION) [FORMAT=TYPE]]                            
		SPLIT                                                                      
	OUTREC = (FIELD-SPEC...)                                                       
	OPTION                                                                         
	       SKIPREC=nn, STOPAFT=nn                                                  
	       VLSCMP VLSHRT EQUALS REMOVECC                                           
___________________________________________________________________________________
Format Type                                                                        
___________________________________________________________________________________
	CH = Char                                                                      
	BI = Binary   binary-byteorder: native                                         
	PD = Packed   binary-byteorder: native                                         
	ZD = Zoned    max 18 digits                                                    
___________________________________________________________________________________
File Organization                                                                  
___________________________________________________________________________________
    LS  = Line Sequential                                                          
    SQ  = Sequential Fixed or Variable (first 4 byte  record len )                 
    SQMF= Sequential (Header file + first 2/4 byte record len )                    
___________________________________________________________________________________
Variables Environment                                                              
___________________________________________________________________________________
OCSORT_EMULATE     Value 0 for OCSORT, 1 for MF Emulator                           
OCSORT_MEMSIZE     Memory Allocation in byte(Default 512000000 byte)                
OCSORT_TESTCMD     Value 0 for normal operations , 1 for ONLY test command line    
OCSORT_DEBUG       Value 0 for normal operations , 1 for DEBUG, 2 for DEBUG Parser 
OCSORT_PATHTMP     Pathname for temporary files							   	       
OCSORT_STATISTICS  0 for normal operations , 1 for Summary, 2 for Details          
___________________________________________________________________________________